# IMDb Clone

This is a simple IMDb Clone web application built using HTML, CSS, and vanilla.js.

## Features

- Search any movie from the API and display the search results on the frontend.
- As you type in the search input, the search results will update dynamically like Google suggestions.
- Each search result movie has a favorite button, clicking on which adds the movie to "My Favourite Movies" list.
- Clicking on any search result movie opens a new page with more information about that movie.
- The movie page displays details such as the movie's name, photo, plot, etc.
- The "My Favourite Movies" page displays a list of all the favorite movies.
- The list of favorite movies is persistent, and it retains the same movies even after closing or refreshing the browser.
- Each movie in the favorite list has a "Remove from Favourites" button to remove the movie from the list.

## Project Structure

The project consists of the following files:

- `index.html`: The home page HTML file that contains the search functionality and displays the search results.
- `styles.css`: The CSS file that provides the styles and layout for the web application.
- `script.js`: The main JavaScript file that handles the search functionality, API requests, and dynamically updating the UI.
- `movie.html`: The movie page HTML file that displays detailed information about a specific movie.
- `movie.js`: The JavaScript file that fetches and displays the movie details on the movie page.

## Usage

To run the IMDb Clone web application, simply open the `index.html` file in a web browser. The application requires an internet connection to fetch movie data from the OMDB API.

## Dependencies

The IMDb Clone project has the following dependencies:

- Bootstrap 4.3.1: A CSS framework used for styling the web application. It is included via a CDN in the HTML files.

